mux.metric: rho_X = corr( (env_X_residual * chip_X), msg ) ; delta = rho_B - rho_C
mux.note: Engineered spread-spectrum AM; selective decoding is a computational primitive, not a physics claim.

definitions.goal: Demonstrate selective listening: B (matching code) decodes message better than C (mismatch) at equal distance in the same broadcast medium.
non_claims: This is engineered comms (spread-spectrum + matched filtering), not quantum entanglement or biological translation.
